  "prompt": "Why should I tip my server?",
  "response": "Tipping your server is customary in many cultures, particularly in the United States, and there are several reasons why it is considered important:\n\n1. **Supplementing Income**: Many servers in restaurants receive a base wage that is below the minimum wage because they rely on tips to make up the difference. Tipping helps ensure they earn a living wage.\n\n2. **Incentive for Good Service**: Tips can motivate servers to provide better customer service. A good tip can encourage them to go above and beyond in their service, which can enhance your dining experience.\n\n3. **Recognition of Effort**: Tipping is a way to acknowledge the hard work and effort that servers put into their jobs, which often includes long hours, multitasking, and handling multiple tables at once.\n\n4. **Cultural Norm**: In places where tipping is customary, not doing so may be seen as rude or disrespectful. Following social norms can help ensure a positive experience for both you and the server.\n\n5. **Encouraging Future Service**: If you typically frequent a restaurant, tipping well can help you build a rapport with your server, who may remember you and provide better service during future visits.\n\n6. **Economic Impact**: Tipping contributes to the service economy, supporting not only servers but also their families and the local economy. It helps sustain jobs in the hospitality industry.\n\nUltimately, the decision to tip should be based on your dining experience and satisfaction with the service provided. If you feel that the service was excellent, tipping generously can reflect that appreciation.",
